#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:13.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.10.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.10.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2077"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:13.2"
msgid "Bhikkhuṃ paneva uddissāti"
msgstr "For a monk:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:13.3"
msgctxt "bhikkhussatthāya, bhikkhuṃ ārammaṇaṃ karitvā, bhikkhuṃ acchādetukāmo."
msgstr "for the benefit of a monk; making a monk the object of consideration, one desires to give to him."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2078"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:14.1"
msgid "Rājā nāma"
msgstr "A king:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:14.2"
msgctxt "yo koci rajjaṃ kāreti."
msgstr "whoever rules."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.67"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2079"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:15.1"
msgid "Rājabhoggo nāma"
msgstr "A king’s employee:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:15.2"
msgctxt "yo koci rañño bhattavetanāhāro."
msgstr "whoever gets food and wages from a king."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2080"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:16.1"
msgid "Brāhmaṇo nāma"
msgstr "A brahmin:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:16.2"
msgctxt "jātiyā brāhmaṇo."
msgstr "a brahmin by birth."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2081"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:17.1"
msgid "Gahapatiko nāma"
msgstr "A householder:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:17.2"
msgctxt "ṭhapetvā rājaṃ rājabhoggaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ avaseso gahapatiko nāma."
msgstr "anyone apart from a king, a king’s employee, and a brahmin."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2082"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:18.1"
msgid "Cīvaracetāpannaṃ nāma"
msgstr "A robe fund:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:18.2"
msgctxt "hiraññaṃ vā suvaṇṇaṃ vā muttā vā maṇi vā."
msgstr "money, gold, a pearl, or a gem."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2083"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:19.1"
msgid "Iminā cīvaracetāpannenāti"
msgstr "With this robe fund:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:19.2"
msgctxt "paccupaṭṭhitena."
msgstr "with that which is at one’s disposal."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2084"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:20.1"
msgid "Cetāpetvāti"
msgstr "Buy:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:20.2"
msgctxt "parivattetvā."
msgstr "having exchanged."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2085"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:21.1"
msgid "Acchādehīti"
msgstr "Give:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:21.2"
msgctxt "dajjehi."
msgstr "donate."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2086"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:22.1"
msgid "So ce dūto taṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr "And the messenger goes to that monk and says,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:22.2"
msgid "“idaṃ kho, bhante, āyasmantaṃ uddissa cīvaracetāpannaṃ ābhataṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable, I have brought a robe fund for you;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:22.3"
msgid "Paṭiggaṇhātu āyasmā cīvaracetāpannan”ti,"
msgstr "please accept it,”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:22.4"
msgid "tena bhikkhunā so dūto evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "then that monk should reply,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:22.5"
msgid "“na kho mayaṃ, āvuso, cīvaracetāpannaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma."
msgstr "“We don’t receive robe funds,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:22.6"
msgid "Cīvarañca kho mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma, kālena kappiyan”ti."
msgstr "but we do receive allowable robes at the right time.”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:22.7"
msgid "So ce dūto taṃ bhikkhuṃ evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr "If that messenger says,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:22.8"
msgid "“atthi panāyasmato koci veyyāvaccakaro”ti?"
msgstr "“Is there anyone who provides services for you?”,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:22.9"
msgid "Cīvaratthikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā veyyāvaccakaro niddisitabbo ārāmiko vā upāsako vā—"
msgstr "the monk, if he needs a robe, should point out a monastery attendant or a lay follower and say,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:22.10"
msgid "“eso kho, āvuso, bhikkhūnaṃ veyyāvaccakaro”ti."
msgstr "“He provides services for the monks”:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:22.11"
msgid "Na vattabbo—"
msgstr "he should not say,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:22.12"
msgid "“tassa dehīti vā, so vā nikkhipissati, so vā parivattessati, so vā cetāpessatī”ti."
msgstr "“Give it to him/he’ll put it aside/he’ll do the exchange/he’ll buy it.”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2087"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:23.1"
msgid "So ce dūto taṃ veyyāvaccakaraṃ saññāpetvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr "If the messenger instructs that service-provider and then returns to the monk and says,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:23.2"
msgid "“yaṃ kho, bhante, āyasmā veyyāvaccakaraṃ niddisi saññatto so mayā."
msgstr "“Venerable, I have instructed the service-provider you pointed out;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:23.3"
msgid "Upasaṅkamatu āyasmā kālena, cīvarena taṃ acchādessatī”ti."
msgstr "please approach him at the right time and he will give you a robe,”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:23.4"
msgid "Cīvaratthikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā veyyāvaccakaro upasaṅkamitvā dvattikkhattuṃ codetabbo sāretabbo—"
msgstr "then, if that monk needs a robe, he should approach that service-provider and prompt him and remind him two or three times, saying,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:23.5"
msgid "“attho me, āvuso, cīvarenā”ti."
msgstr "“I need a robe”:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:23.6"
msgid "Na vattabbo—"
msgstr "he should not say,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:23.7"
msgid "“dehi me cīvaraṃ, āhara me cīvaraṃ, parivattehi me cīvaraṃ, cetāpehi me cīvaran”ti."
msgstr "“Give me a robe/get me a robe/get a robe in exchange for me/buy me a robe.”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.223"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2088"></a><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:24.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi vattabbo."
msgstr "He should say it a second"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:24.2"
msgid "Tatiyampi vattabbo."
msgstr "and a third time."

#. </span></p><p><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:24.3"
msgid "Sace abhinipphādeti, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If he gets it, that is good."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:24.4"
msgid "no ce abhinipphādeti, tattha gantvā tuṇhībhūtena uddissa ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he does not get it, [he should go there and] he should stand in silence for it:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:24.5"
msgid "Na āsane nisīditabbaṃ."
msgstr "he should not sit down on a seat."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:24.6"
msgid "Na āmisaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ."
msgstr "He should not accept a gift."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.68"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:24.7"
msgid "Na dhammo bhāsitabbo."
msgstr "He should not give a teaching."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:24.8"
msgid "“Kiṃ kāraṇā āgatosī”ti pucchiyamāno"
msgstr "If he is asked, “Why have you come?”,"

#. <span class="note" hidden><i lang="pi">Jānāhi</i>. This verb, which normally means “to understand” or “to find out,” is used quite broadly in the Pali canon.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:24.9"
msgid "“jānāhi, āvuso”ti vattabbo."
msgstr "he should say, “Think about it.”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:24.10"
msgid "Sace āsane vā nisīdati, āmisaṃ vā paṭiggaṇhāti, dhammaṃ vā bhāsati, ṭhānaṃ bhañjati."
msgstr "If he sits down on a seat, or he accepts a gift, or he gives a teaching, he loses one allowance to stand."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2089"></a><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:25.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "He should stand a second"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:25.2"
msgid "Tatiyampi ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "and a third time."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:25.3"
msgid "Catukkhattuṃ codetvā catukkhattuṃ ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he prompts four times, he can stand four times."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:25.4"
msgid "Pañcakkhattuṃ codetvā dvikkhattuṃ ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he prompts five times, he can stand twice."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:25.5"
msgid "Chakkhattuṃ codetvā na ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he prompts six times, he cannot stand at all."

#. </span></p><hr><p><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.10.2.2"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:25.6"
msgid "Tato ce uttari vāyamamāno taṃ cīvaraṃ abhinipphādeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr "If he makes any further effort and the robe then appears, he commits an offense of wrong conduct for the effort."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:25.7"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the robe, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.69"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:25.8"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe should be relinquished to the Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:25.9"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="add"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:25.10"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in <a href=\"/en/pi-tv-bu-vb-np1#13\">Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:25.11"
msgid "“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ atirekatikkhattuṃ codanāya atirekachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena abhinipphāditaṃ nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, this robe which I got after prompting more than three times and standing more than six times is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:25.12"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:25.13"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:25.14"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:25.15"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe back to you.’”"

#. </span></p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2090"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:26.1"
msgid "No ce abhinipphādeyya, yatassa cīvaracetāpannaṃ ābhataṃ tattha sāmaṃ vā gantabbaṃ dūto vā pāhetabbo—"
msgstr "If he does not get a robe, he should go to the owner of that robe fund, or send a message:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:26.2"
msgid "“yaṃ kho tumhe, āyasmanto, bhikkhuṃ uddissa cīvaracetāpannaṃ pahiṇittha na taṃ tassa bhikkhuno kiñci atthaṃ anubhoti."
msgstr "‘Sirs, that monk hasn’t received any benefit from the robe fund you sent for him."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:26.3"
msgid "Yuñjantāyasmanto sakaṃ,"
msgstr "Please take action over what’s yours;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:26.4"
msgid "mā vo sakaṃ vinassā”ti."
msgstr "let it not be lost.’"

#. </strong></p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2091"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:27.1"
msgid "Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcīti"
msgstr "This is the proper procedure:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:27.2"
msgctxt "ayaṃ tattha anudhammatā."
msgstr "this is the right method."

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:28.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.10.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2092"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:28.2"
msgid "Atirekatikkhattuṃ codanāya atirekachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena atirekasaññī abhinipphādeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he prompts more than three times and stands more than six times, and he perceives that he has done so, and he gets a robe, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:28.3"
msgid "Atirekatikkhattuṃ codanāya atirekachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena vematiko abhinipphādeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he prompts more than three times and stands more than six times, but he is unsure if he has, and he gets a robe, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:28.4"
msgid "Atirekatikkhattuṃ codanāya atirekachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena ūnakasaññī abhinipphādeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he prompts more than three times and stands more than six times, but he perceives that it is less, and he gets a robe, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2093"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:29.1"
msgid "Ūnakatikkhattuṃ codanāya ūnakachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena atirekasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he prompts less than three times and stands less than six times, but he perceives that it is more, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:29.2"
msgid "Ūnakatikkhattuṃ codanāya ūnakachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he prompts less than three times and stands less than six times, but he is unsure if he has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:29.3"
msgid "Ūnakatikkhattuṃ codanāya ūnakachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena ūnakasaññī anāpatti."
msgstr "If he prompts less than three times and stands less than six times, and he perceives that it is less, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:30.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.10.2.4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2094"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:30.2"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:30.3"
msgid "tikkhattuṃ codanāya, chakkhattuṃ ṭhānena,"
msgstr "if he prompts three times and stands six time;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.70"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:30.4"
msgid "ūnakatikkhattuṃ codanāya, ūnakachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena,"
msgstr "if he prompts less than three times and stands less than six times;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:30.5"
msgid "acodiyamāno deti,"
msgstr "if it is given without prompting;"

#. <span class="note" hidden>I am unable to make sense of the phrasing in the non-offense clause (<i lang="pi">sāmikā codetvā denti</i>), and I therefore translate according to the phrasing in the commentary, “After prompting by the owners, it is given;” <i lang="pi">sāmikehi codetvā dinne</i>, see <span class="ref">Kkh. 119.6</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:30.6"
msgid "sāmikā codetvā denti,"
msgstr "if the owners prompt and then it is given;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:30.7"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:30.8"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2095"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:31.1"
msgid "Rājasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr "The tenth rule, the training rule on kings, is finished."

#. </p><p class="endchapter"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:31.2"
msgid "Kathinavaggo paṭhamo."
msgstr "The first chapter on the robe-making season is finished."

#. </p><p class="endsection summary"><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2096"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:32.1"
msgid "Tassuddānaṃ"
msgstr "This is the summary:"

#. </p><p class="uddana"><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2097"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:33.1"
msgid "Ubbhataṃ kathinaṃ tīṇi,"
msgstr "Three on the ended robe-making season,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:33.2"
msgid "dhovanañca paṭiggaho;"
msgstr "And washing, receiving;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:33.3"
msgid "Aññātakāni tīṇeva,"
msgstr "Three on those who are unrelated,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np10:33.4"
msgid "ubhinnaṃ dūtakena cāti."
msgstr "Of both, and with messenger."

